.RH MOD.RECIPES-SOURCE SPINACH-DIP A "9 Apr 86" 1986
.RZ "SPINACH DIP" "Party dip with spinach and water chestnuts"
People like this dip.  It's a hit a parties.
It is good to dip vegetables into, or to spread on crackers.
.IH "makes 4 cups" "makes 1 liter"
.IG "1 cup" "sour cream" "250 ml"
.IG "1 cup" "mayonnaise" "250 ml"
.IG "8 oz" "water chestnuts," "250 g"
drained and diced (one large can)
.IG "5" "green onions,"
chopped (with tops)
.IG "10 oz" "cooked spinach," "300 g"
drained well. Use one package of frozen spinach.
.IG "1 envelope" "Knorr dry vegetable soup mix,"
(a Swiss import)
.PH
.SK 1
Mix everything together and refrigerate overnight.
.SK 2
Stir again before serving.
.NX
Serve with sturdy dip-ables or crackers, as it will break chips.
.SH RATING
.I Difficulty:
trivial.
.I Time:
15 minutes preparation.
.I Precision:
Approximate measurement OK.
.WR
